            - I have some mixed feelings about this book. It's the first book I'm reading by Murakami, and the audio production was great. The book has some Tolstoy feeling in it, as in, it does something psychologically to you, but I'm not exactly sure what. I also don't know how much I can trust Murakami, to open myself up to let him do what I don't know what it is. That said, it was a very engaging book that touched on a million small topics with one big theme sorrounding them all. The stream of consciousness at the beginning and slowly the multiple stories joining with each other is very exciting. The characters are consistent throughout the book and everything goes on logically, though a logic that is not feasible in our world, but is consistent. And eventually everything becoming like a dream or even a nightmare maybe. There is an erotic theme that is secondary to the story throughout most of the book and tries to become the maim story, but always something else happens and it goes away, until at some point you realize that it has become the main theme. Quite a new experience for sure.
