            - The book is a selection of poems that are reflecting 4 different personas that Pessoa takes on, bit seemingly there just 4 different pen names over periods of his life and at times they came back. There are some poems that I can really feel, and there are some that I don't even understand what they're about, I blame the latter on translation, and not particularly on Griffin's because translating poems is just impossible, or at least Apollinaire thought so. A lot of the poems are from later in his life 1931-1935. Some of the poems just feel like he's boasting about how intellectual he thinks he is or how philosophical he can get, or how much of snob he can be. So many times using the term "metaphysics"!?! What does that even mean? Anyways, many other ones are very pleasant to read. Tobacconist's and the one about Newton are my favorites.
