reading list
    [] The age of surveillance capitalism
        - author: Shoshana Zuboff
        - year: 2018
        - goodreads: https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26195941
        - goodreads rating: 4.05
        - review
            - 2024-04-16: This is a reaaaaally long book, and really dark, but that just says how deep in trouble we are. While it didn't have too many news for me, I learned quite a few things and it put things in a very robust perspective, drawing parallels to what we have experienced in history, and what is new to us and is being experienced for the first time. I wish the language was a bit less of a doomsday-sayer's one so that I could easily recommend this to most others to read, but I think when there's fire there's no other way of announcing it by yelling fire. I would still say anyone who has ever touched a smartphone or a computer should read this book. There's too much to discuss, but one of the things that I really liked is how she explains the situation we are in with a huge amount of clarity, and then her restless effort of translating what goes into terms of services that we sign, the lack of any laws to govern the tech industry, and that how we are OK with all of this. A much smaller piece but still an enjoyable part is how she dismantles the "if it's free, then you're the product" and replaces it with "if it's free you're the raw material", and clarifies the distinction.
